<sect1 id="TZDataForLocation">
  <!--This is a template for STD library method mod files-->

  <title>TZDataForLocation</title>

  <para><emphasis role="bold">STD.Date.TimeZone.TZDataForLocation<indexterm>
      <primary>STD.Date.TimeZone.TZDataForLocation</primary>
    </indexterm><indexterm>
      <primary>TimeZone.TZDataForLocation</primary>
    </indexterm><indexterm>
      <primary>TZDataForLocation</primary>
    </indexterm>(</emphasis> <emphasis>location </emphasis> <emphasis
  role="bold">)</emphasis></para>

  <informaltable colsep="1" frame="all" rowsep="1">
    <tgroup cols="2">
      <colspec colwidth="80.50pt" />

      <colspec />

      <tbody>
        <row>
          <entry><emphasis>location</emphasis></entry>

          <entry>REQUIRED. The name of the location to search for; must be a
          non-empty uppercase string. </entry>
        </row>

        <row>
          <entry>Returns:</entry>

          <entry>A new DATASET(STRING5 tzAbbrev, INTEGER4 secondsOffset)
          containing the records found for the given location.</entry>
        </row>
      </tbody>
    </tgroup>
  </informaltable>

  <para>The <emphasis
  role="bold">STD.Date.TimeZone.TZDataForLocation</emphasis> function returns
  the time zone records for a given location.</para>

  <para>Example:</para>

  <programlisting format="linespecific">IMPORT STD;
STD.Date.TimeZone.TZDataForLocation('ASIA');</programlisting>

  <para>See Also: <link linkend="FindTZData">FindTZData</link></para>
</sect1>
